Use Cases:
UC1 — View session schedule
UC2 — Select seat
UC3 — Book tickets
UC4 — Cancel booking
UC5 — Save customer data
UC6 — Print ticket
UC7 — Manage movies
UC8 — Manage sessions
UC9 — Manage halls
UC10 — Manage seats
UC11 — Process payment

Functional Requirements:
FR1 — Display movie sessions schedule
FR2 — Show available seats selection
FR3 — Create booking with customer data
FR4 — Cancel existing booking
FR5 — Store and update customer information
FR6 — Generate printable tickets
FR7 — Maintain movie catalog
FR8 — Manage session timetables
FR9 — Configure cinema halls
FR10 — Manage seat arrangements
FR11 — Process payment transactions

Non-Functional Requirements:
NFR1 — Data integrity through foreign keys (Customer→Booking→Ticket)
NFR2 — Response time ≤ 3 seconds for booking operations
NFR3 — Transaction consistency for payment processing
NFR4 — System availability during cinema working hours
NFR5 — Web interface compatibility for customers
NFR6 — Secure payment gateway integration